          "type": "text",
          "text": "Perfect! ✓ **7-segment counter circuit created.**\n\n**How it works:**\n- **Arduino pins 2–8** drive the 7 segments (a–g) through 220Ω current-limiting resistors.\n- **Pin 9** connects to a button pulled LOW on press (INPUT_PULLUP).\n- **Logic**: When the button transitions from HIGH→LOW, the counter increments and wraps 0→9→0 using modulo (%). Each number 0–9 has a hardcoded segment pattern (standard 7-segment truth table).\n- **GND rail**: Distributes ground to both the display's common cathode and the button's second pin.\n\nPress the button to watch the display count up—it'll roll back to 0 after 9."
        }
      ]
    }
